@startuml ticket-creation-references-sla
title Ticket Creation With References and SLA Snapshot
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Agent" as Agent
participant "Ticket UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Ticket\nController" as Controller
participant "Ticket\nService" as TicketService
participant "Reference\nService" as RefService
participant "Reference Models\nWorkspace/Mailbox/Contact/\nOrg/Category/Tag/Member" as RefModels
participant "SLA Runtime\nService" as SlaRuntime
participant "SLA Models\nPolicy/BusinessHours" as SlaModels
participant "Ticket Models\nCounter/Ticket/Conversation" as TicketModels
participant "Message/File\nServices" as MessageFileServices
participant "Billing Usage +\nLive Events" as Events

== 1. Submit ticket create ==
Agent -> UI: Fill ticket form
UI -> Routes: POST /api/tickets
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nowner/admin/agent role
Routes -> Routes: validate createTicket body
Routes -> Controller: createTicketController(req)
Controller -> TicketService: createTicket(workspaceId,\ncreatedByUserId, payload)

== 2. Resolve references ==
TicketService -> RefService: load workspace and resolve mailbox\n(provided or workspace default)
RefService -> RefModels: find active same-workspace mailbox
TicketService -> RefService: validate contact, organization,\ncategory, tags, assignee
RefService -> RefModels: load active same-workspace references

== 3. Snapshot SLA ==
TicketService -> SlaRuntime: resolveTicketSlaSnapshot(workspace,\nmailbox, priority)
alt Effective SLA policy exists
  SlaRuntime -> SlaModels: load active policy\nand business hours
  SlaRuntime --> TicketService: SLA snapshot with targets,\ndue dates, business-hours copy
else No effective SLA
  SlaRuntime --> TicketService: empty SLA snapshot
end

== 4. Create ticket and conversation ==
TicketService -> TicketModels: allocate workspace ticket number
TicketService -> TicketModels: create Ticket with references,\nstatus, number, sla snapshot
TicketService -> TicketModels: create Conversation and save\nticket.conversationId
TicketService -> MessageFileServices: if initialMessage exists,\ncreate message and link attachments

== 5. Publish and update usage ==
TicketService -> Events: increment tickets-created usage\n(best effort)
TicketService -> Events: publish ticket.created\nand message events when needed
TicketService --> Controller: hydrated ticket detail
Controller --> UI: success.ticket.created
UI --> Agent: Show created ticket

@enduml
